\title{Meet semilattice}
\taxon{definition}

\p{A \em{meet semilattice} is a set #{S} with a binary operation #{\land} called a \em{meet} such that, for all #{x,y,z \in S}}

\ul{
\li{Associativity: #{x \land (y \land z) = (x \land y)\land z}}
\li{Commutativity: #{x \land y = y \land x}}
\li{Idempotency: #{x \land x = x}}}

\p{This can be equivalently thought of as extending a preorder with [meets](math-006A) for all pairs of elements.}
